Reference-contexts: In this letter, we describe a hybrid integrated laser-to-fiber coupling module with an on-chip micromachined alignment micromirror. The micromirror has two degrees of freedom and is able to compensate for both horizontal and vertical component misalignment. When combined with on-chip microvibromotor actuators <ref> [5] </ref>, the micromirror will become a (a) lens micromirror fiber laser (b) and the completed coupling module (b). 2 key component in a self-aligned microphotonic module. We have characterized the positioning precision of the micromirror using an external motorized actuator and achieved a coupling efficiency of 40%.
