Reference-contexts: Our prototype module is designed for a nominal magnification of M=4 to achieve a balance between peak coupling efficiency and precision constraints. Fabrication and Testing The movable micromirror is fabricated using silicon-surface micromachining technology <ref> [ 6] </ref>. Microhinges [ 7,8] provide the mirror with rotational freedom of motion and a large aspect ratio ( Figure 1 a). Two sliders control the angular and translational positions of the micromirror. Three 2 m m-thick structural polysilicon layers compose the sliders, hinges, and mirror plates.
